15
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:33,450
{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第五季  第十集

16
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:50,340
我爷爷说  死人不瞑目
The dead sleep with their eyes open, my grandfather would say.

17
00:02:50,350 --> 00:02:52,990
他们从过去注视着你
They're watching you from the past...

18
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:54,380
杰姬·夏普
Jackie Sharp.

19
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,430
罗梅洛一刻都没浪费
Romero wasted no time.

20
00:02:56,590 --> 00:02:57,530
你有什么用
What good are you?

21
00:02:57,530 --> 00:02:59,770
你们民主党人真是惊喜不断
You Democrats are full of surprises.

22
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:01,740
她的律师不让我们靠近她
Her lawyers won't let us get anywhere near her.

23
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:03,620
因为他们在商量她的证词
Because they're negotiating her testimony.

24
00:03:03,620 --> 00:03:05,320
我们到底是怎么到这一步的
How the hell did we get here?

25
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:09,310
罗梅洛知道消息  党内有人给他通风报信
Romero was privy to information. Someone from within the party.

26
00:03:09,550 --> 00:03:11,220
他威胁要追究她拉票
He's threatening to go after her for whipping votes

27
00:03:11,220 --> 00:03:14,750
来换取雷米·丹顿先生的竞选经费一事
in exchange for campaign funds from a Mr. Remy Danton,

28
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,800
令人"震惊"的是她和雷米上过床
who, shockingly, she was sleeping with.

29
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,890
她不会因为一段婚外情就作证
Well, she's not testifying because of an affair.

30
00:03:18,890 --> 00:03:21,040
她作证是因为她不想进监狱
She's testifying 'cause she doesn't want to go to jail.

31
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:23,160
任何人出庭作证都只因为这个
Which is the only reason anyone testifies.

32
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,330
道格  盯住委员会里剩下的民主党人
Doug, keep at the rest of the Democrats on that committee.

33
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:27,710
确保他们守规矩
Make sure they stay in line.

34
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:31,420
我会在我党这边发力  但  罗梅洛
I'll keep working my side of the aisle, but... uh, Romero.

35
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,470
他是个混蛋
He's a prick.

36
00:03:32,470 --> 00:03:34,630
一个依然想当党鞭的混蛋
Mmm-hmm, prick who still wants whip.

37
00:03:35,170 --> 00:03:36,770
泰瑞·乌麦克一直忠心耿耿
Terry Womack has been very loyal.

38
00:03:36,770 --> 00:03:39,970
是啊  忠诚和厉害是两码事
Yeah, well, there's loyal, and then there's good.

39
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,340
乌麦克给了你什么
What has Womack brought you?

40
00:03:42,710 --> 00:03:44,690
宣战委员会是他解决的吗
Did he kill the Declaration of War Committee?

41
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,010
11月时他帮你拿下密苏里了吗
Did he deliver Missouri for you in November?

42
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:48,160
够了
That's enough.

43
00:03:49,610 --> 00:03:50,710
满足他吧
Let's give it to him.

44
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:52,410
有时你得做出艰难抉择
Look, sometimes you have to make hard choices.

45
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:53,910
我会跟泰瑞谈的
I'll talk to Terry.

46
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:56,980
罗梅洛得给他找个地方落脚
Romero's gonna have to find a place for him to land, and...

47
00:03:57,380 --> 00:03:59,300
落在哪我是在意的
where that is matters to me.

48
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,820
就这样吧
That'll be all for now.

49
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:02,800
好  先生
Yes, sir.

50
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:15,170
我会让道尔去查
I'm gonna put Doyle on this.

51
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:17,880
我们已经审查过罗梅洛了
We already vetted Romero.

52
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:19,880
不  我是说查厄舍
No, I mean on Usher.

53
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:23,740
尸体保存得非常完好
The body is remarkably well-preserved,

54
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:26,480
除了手脚  因为都冻伤了
except for the extremities, which frostbite took care of.

55
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,000
但牙齿是完好的
But dental is intact.

56
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,290
我们在南极的同行正在全力配合
Our counterparts in Antarctica are cooperating fully,

57
00:04:30,290 --> 00:04:33,250
12小时内尸体会到我们手上
and the body will be in our possession within the next 12 hours.

58
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:34,860
报关后我会派人把它运回来
I'll have it in transit after customs.

59
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:38,040
我们希望尸体在运输中失踪
We'd like the body to get lost in transit.

60
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:38,980
女士
Ma'am?

61
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:41,170
它必须失踪
It needs to get lost.

62
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:42,730
好
Yes.

63
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:46,730
好  谢谢  助理局长格林
Okay. Thank you, Assistant Director Green.

64
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,300
我们再联系
Uh, keep in touch.

65
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:57,660
-我还以为你已经睡了  -还不能睡
- I thought you'd gone to bed. - Can't yet.

66
00:05:01,090 --> 00:05:03,090
-那是谁  -我们不认识
- Who's that? - No one we know.

67
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:08,740
汤姆  我说了  我们不认识
Tom, I said it's no one we know.

68
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,830
你听说过他们在意大利阿尔卑斯山发现的
You ever hear about the 5,000-year-old man they found

69
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:19,640
冰冻五千年的干尸吗
frozen in the Italian Alps?

70
00:05:20,650 --> 00:05:21,550
没有
No.

71
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:26,070
他的头骨后面被砸出了坑
His skull was caved in... from the back.

72
00:05:27,130 --> 00:05:28,720
他大概根本没料到
He probably never saw it coming.

73
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:34,520
被痛打一顿  留下等死
Beaten and left for dead.

74
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:40,750
留下等死是一个古老的概念
Left for dead is an ancient concept.

75
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,330
当人被冻死的时候
You know, when you freeze to death...

76
00:05:44,990 --> 00:05:49,070
最后会感觉非常热
the last thing you feel is extreme heat.

77
00:05:49,070 --> 00:05:50,250
疼
That hurts.

78
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:51,680
抱歉
Sorry.

79
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:57,450
我刚看到了弗兰西斯
I saw Francis out there.

80
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:00,270
他好像很焦躁
He seems on edge.

81
00:06:02,610 --> 00:06:03,750
能怪他吗
Can you blame him?

82
00:06:06,570 --> 00:06:07,460
好点了吗
Better?

83
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,600
最重的罪是入店行窃
Shoplifting is the worst of it.

84
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:35,480
近来几次在街上买毒品  而被法庭强制戒毒
A couple of recent street buys that led to court-mandated rehab.

85
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:40,100
她就在那里生活  工作  买毒品
That's where she lives, where she works, where she scores...

86
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:44,530
但依我看就是个二十多的女人  努力想活到三十
But all I see here is a woman in her 20s, trying to get to 30.

87
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:48,400
-她是个威胁  -我不懂
- She's a concern. - I don't get it.

88
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:51,480
嘉文·奥尔西去委内瑞拉之前  她和他有联系
She was in touch with Gavin Orsay before he left for Venezuela.

89
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,150
-道格  -纳森
- Doug... - Nathan!

90
00:06:54,270 --> 00:06:56,970
你的语气有点急  我们可能得讨论下
There's a bite to your tone that we might need to discuss.

91
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:01,900
她是个隐患  是个瘾君子
She's a loose end and an addict.

92
00:07:03,670 --> 00:07:05,290
这两样合在一起很糟
That's a bad combination.

93
00:07:09,650 --> 00:07:10,840
重新装修了
It's a clean slate.

94
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,170
唐纳德·布莱斯的品味对我来说太暗了
Donald Blythe's taste was a bit too dark for me,

95
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:15,870
所以我全拆掉了
so I stripped it all back.

96
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:20,570
我选了一副画  还在路上
I have chosen one painting so far that's on its way, though.

97
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,800
撒德·彼得森的尸体处理好了
Thad Peterson's body is taken care of.

98
00:07:24,310 --> 00:07:26,150
他叫无名氏
His name is John Doe.

99
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:29,140
他化成灰我都认识
I'd recognize him anywhere.

100
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:33,800
这本来会伤害到我国的
This would've been very embarrassing to some interests

101
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,280
一些重要利益
that are important to this country.

102
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:38,140
我也不希望他的家人看到他这样
And I wouldn't want the family to see him this way.

103
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:41,480
约旦大使馆有什么消息
What's the news from the Jordanian Embassy?

104
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:44,530
艾丹·麦卡伦仍不愿
Aidan Macallan still won't

105
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:47,680
透露他跟佩特洛夫说了什么  没说什么
reveal what he did or didn't tell Petrov.

106
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,450
总统希望他立刻从避难地
Well, the president wants him brought back from his asylum

107
00:07:50,450 --> 00:07:51,970
回到美国
to the United States immediately.

108
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:53,880
我们应该耐心点儿
I think we should give it a little more time.

109
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:58,520
我在想让你插手明不明智
You know, I wonder if it was such a good idea to bring you in on this.

110
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,570
-你承诺了  -我知道  艾哈迈迪...
- You promised-- - I know. Ahmadi...

111
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:06,070
我们派了特种部队去当地追踪
We've got Special Forces on the ground, tracking.

112
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,510
俄罗斯在叙利亚的存在
Russia's presence in Syria

113
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:10,030
让此事比我曾经想得要复杂
is making this more difficult than I once thought.

114
00:08:10,030 --> 00:08:13,110
我得知道麦卡伦跟佩特罗夫说了什么
I need to know what Macallan told Petrov.

115
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,210
男人制造烂摊子的天赋
It never ceases to astonish me

116
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:18,360
总能让我吃惊
how talented men are at making a mess.

117
00:08:32,920 --> 00:08:35,460
打击同党对你来说可没好处
Uh, it's not gonna serve you to go after your own party.

118
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,040
你从不放弃
You never stop.

119
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,960
杰姬·夏普不会作证的
Jackie Sharp will never testify.

120
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,640
那她就得进监狱
Well, then she'll go to jail.

121
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:46,100
艾力克斯  你证明不了他们之间有交换条件
You can't prove it, Alex. You can't prove the quid pro quo.

122
00:08:46,430 --> 00:08:47,910
她好像觉得我可以
She seems to think I can.

123
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:50,150
如果你换种方式
If you play it a little differently,

124
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,350
还有机会实现目标
you have a chance to get what you want.

125
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:52,660
我们可以给你党鞭的位子
We're offering you whip.

126
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:56,090
-我不想要了  -什么
- I don't want it anymore. - What?

127
00:08:57,050 --> 00:08:58,460
天啊
Jesus Christ.

128
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,220
那就财政委员会
Ways and Means, then.

129
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,310
在下次党代会上做主讲
The keynote at the next convention.

130
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:06,680
我只想让弗兰西斯·安德伍德进监狱
What I want is for Francis Underwood to go to jail.

131
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,350
天呐  这对你有什么好处
My God. How is that gonna help you?

132
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:11,140
真的  这对你有什么好处
Really? How's it gonna help you?

133
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:17,290
还有别的办法做到
There's another way to go at it.

134
00:09:19,470 --> 00:09:20,890
你想扬名
Wanna make a name for yourself?

135
00:09:21,650 --> 00:09:23,540
你想让总统生不如死
You wanna make the president's life a living hell?

136
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:24,450
那就慢慢来
Draw it out.

137
00:09:24,820 --> 00:09:27,360
让委员会继续  但要温水煮青蛙
Keep the committee going but at a slow burn.

138
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,130
你不是为他工作吗
Aren't you working for him?

139
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:32,040
政府成员  一次找一个人
Members of the administration, you bring 'em in one at a time.

140
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:35,350
你可以纠缠几年  一边稳住自己的地位
You could ride this for a couple of years and secure your place.

141
00:09:35,610 --> 00:09:37,510
而你压制住总统
While you keep the president in check.

142
00:09:38,450 --> 00:09:41,090
别传唤杰姬·夏普  否则计划会胎死腹中
Don't end it before it's begun by calling Jackie Sharp.

143
00:09:41,090 --> 00:09:42,500
你知道我看好你
You know I see good things for you.

144
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,930
让我为你规划接下来的八年
Let me plan out your next eight years.

145
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:48,100
与你合作的候选人
The candidates you worked with...

146
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:52,550
他们中有多少人反复等待
how many of them have waited and waited

147
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,180
误了时机
and lost their moment?

148
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:58,190
嗯  没错
Yeah, that's right.

149
00:09:58,830 --> 00:10:01,370
我分析当下时局  现在属于我
I'm reading the moment, and this is mine.

150
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:03,420
让我在第三街下车
Let me out on Third Street.

151
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,140
我送你到雷伯恩大楼
I'll drop you at Rayburn.

152
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:07,200
不  我总是走最后46米
No, I always walk the final 50 yards.

153
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,490
可能有机会做政治交际
Never know when you might get a chance to press some flesh.

154
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,830
是啊
Yeah.

155
00:10:10,950 --> 00:10:13,540
你好  我是艾力克斯·罗梅洛
Hi, I'm Alex Romero.

156
00:10:13,540 --> 00:10:15,840
我代表亚利桑那州第七区
I represent the Seventh District of Arizona.

157
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,210
我想知道你昨晚失眠的原因
I want to know what keeps you up at night,

158
00:10:17,210 --> 00:10:19,230
我今天好解决这一问题
so I can work all day to address it.

159
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:21,110
未来属于我们所有人
The future belongs to all of us.

160
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,200
但愿我能得到你的支持
I hope I can count on your support.

161
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,730
你觉得怎么样  马克
What do you think, Mark?

162
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:29,590
你可是专家
I mean, you're the expert.

163
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,060
就这儿
Right here.

164
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,190
罗梅洛拒绝了  一般的条件他也不感兴趣
Romero said no, and the usual offers don't interest him.

165
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:38,510
他感兴趣  你只是恨自己感兴趣
Oh, he's interested. He just hates himself for it.

166
00:10:38,510 --> 00:10:41,250
关于委员会的共和党人  我有了进展
I am making headway with the Republicans on the committee.

167
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:44,400
他们都有不可告人的过去  大多有目击证人
They all have pasts, most of them have witnesses.

168
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,890
无论如何  杰姬·夏普不会作证
One way or another, Jackie Sharp won't be testifying.

169
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,360
那你为什么这么难搞定
So why are you having so much trouble

170
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,150
这位年轻议员
with this one young congressman?

171
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,540
他很固执
He's tenacious.

172
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:54,040
他让我想起了你
He reminds me of you.

173
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:57,140
我根本看不出来  我们再联系
Well, I don't see that at all. We'll talk later.

174
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:00,260
我可以联系丹顿
I could reach out to Danton--

175
00:11:00,260 --> 00:11:02,480
我们曝光他  他就会曝光我们
We expose him, he'll expose us.

176
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:04,180
那你有什么建议
Well, then what do you suggest?

177
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:06,130
继续做总统该做的事
That I go on being presidential.

178
00:11:06,130 --> 00:11:08,260
我只有这一个办法
That's the only way that I can deal with this.

179
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:10,950
我的就职头百天啊
It's my first 100 days, for God's sake.

180
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:12,950
弗兰西斯
Francis...

181
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:16,090
我们会捉住艾哈迈迪的
we're going to get our hands on Ahmadi.

182
00:11:16,090 --> 00:11:18,220
世界上再多的艾哈迈迪
There aren't enough Ahmadis in the world.

183
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:19,910
也抵不掉我们做的那些事
Not for all we've done.

184
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:21,300
那怎么办
Then what?

185
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:26,390
比如毁了罗梅洛  这件事总能办到吧
Destroy Romero, for one. Can we at least take care of that?

186
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,570
然后毁谁  整个民主党吗
And then who? The rest of the Democratic Party?

187
00:11:28,570 --> 00:11:31,070
我知道我在做什么  克莱尔  我当过总统
I know what I'm doing, Claire. I've been president before.

188
00:11:31,070 --> 00:11:32,250
我也当过
So have I.

189
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:34,930
给我接泰瑞·乌麦克
Get me Terry Womack.

190
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,990
你作为副总统的职责是给我建议
Your job as vice president is to advise.

191
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:41,350
做决定是我的职责
My job is to make the decisions.

192
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:46,830
泰瑞  没错  我就是问问情况
Terry, yes, I'm just checking in.

193
00:11:50,590 --> 00:11:52,660
我希望你知道我们都支持你
Well, I want you to know that we support you.

194
00:11:52,660 --> 00:11:55,720
那混蛋还想当党鞭  做梦去吧
That bastard asked for whip, but that's never gonna happen.

195
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:58,280
只要我在台上就别想  我把话给你撂这儿
Not while I'm in this office. I wanted to assure you.

196
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,750
我一向在能出力的地方帮忙
I've always tried to help where I can.

197
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:02,970
你在卫生和人类服务部帮不上忙吗
And you couldn't help at Health and Human Services?

198
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:06,670
我们这里做了很多了不起的事
The agency does some amazing work.

199
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:11,040
你接受采访时曾说那是你梦寐以求的工作
Well, you were quoted as, uh, calling your position a dream job.

200
00:12:11,630 --> 00:12:13,820
人是可以有多个梦想的
It's possible to have more than one dream.

201
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,390
我可以让助手带你逛逛
I can have my assistant give you a tour.

202
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:19,750
给你看看海地发来的视频
Uh, show you some of the video from Haiti

203
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:22,560
拍的是过去几个月  我们在那边的
and some of the work that we've been doing there

204
00:12:22,570 --> 00:12:24,530
工作和成绩
over the last several months.

205
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:26,220
我一定会把
I will be sure to include

206
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:28,080
你们组织写进我的报道
your organization in the piece I'm writing.

207
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,490
-我相信你们的事业  -谢谢
- I believe in the work you're doing here. - Thank you.

208
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:34,210
和安德伍德政府合作  感觉怎么样
What was it like, uh, working with the Underwood administration?

209
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:37,950
他们还行  且这么说吧
They were fine. Let's leave it at that.

210
00:12:40,730 --> 00:12:43,180
我采访过许多非常棒的组织
You know, I've met with, uh, many wonderful organizations so far.

211
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:47,870
-弗州儿童守卫基金  -他们的工作很棒
- The Virginia Children's Defense Fund. - They do some great work.

212
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:49,860
塔伯特联盟
The Talbot League?

213
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:51,280
这个组织也很棒
Another terrific group.

214
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:56,310
还有安东尼·莫雷蒂纪念基金
The Anthony Moretti Memorial Fund.

215
00:12:58,420 --> 00:13:01,100
他们我倒没什么了解
I don't know anything about them.

216
00:13:02,370 --> 00:13:04,320
他们是器官移植宣传组织
Organ transplantation awareness.

217
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,280
是吗
Oh, is that right?

218
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:15,470
非常抱歉
I'm so sorry.

219
00:13:16,790 --> 00:13:19,480
太失礼了  但我又太饿了
It's rude, but I was famished.

220
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:22,350
谢谢你肯来见我  我给你拿菜单
Thank you for meeting me. Let me get you a menu.

221
00:13:22,350 --> 00:13:25,120
谢谢不用了  我随后还有午餐会
Uh, no, thank you. I have a lunch right after this.

222
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:28,870
那就好  一定要有个吃午饭的地方
Good. You should always have one on the books.

223
00:13:35,850 --> 00:13:38,340
-戴维斯女士  -你担心艾丹
- Miss Davis? - You're worried about Aidan.

224
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,450
你称呼他有什么昵称吗
Do you call him anything for short?

225
00:13:42,950 --> 00:13:44,160
为什么问我这个
Why would you ask me that?

226
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,200
我不知道总统或者副总统
I don't know if the president, or vice president,

227
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,420
告没告诉你  但麦卡挺好的
has informed you, but Mac is fine.

228
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:52,210
问题在于他知道什么
It's what he knows is the problem,

229
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:54,140
他都跟谁说过
and who he may have told it to.

230
00:13:55,530 --> 00:13:57,440
他只想活下去
He wants to stay alive.

231
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,730
没错
Yes.

232
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:03,720
但这种人才得小心
But those are the ones you have to watch out for.

233
00:14:06,170 --> 00:14:09,390
我上次和艾丹说完话他就上了出租车
Last I spoke to Aidan was minutes before he got in a cab.

234
00:14:09,910 --> 00:14:12,040
我不知道他有什么  也不知道他做了什么
I don't know what he has or what he's done.

235
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,820
我只是奉命行事
I only do what I'm told.

236
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,500
我就在胡佛大楼上班
I'm in the Hoover Building.

237
00:14:18,010 --> 00:14:20,620
那真是全城最丑的一栋楼
It's the ugliest building in... in the city.

238
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:22,830
我每次进去都闭着眼
I close my eyes as I walk in.

239
00:14:23,950 --> 00:14:27,280
有空来坐坐  尤其是你想找人谈谈的时候
Stop by any time. Especially if you're in the mood to talk.

240
00:14:27,380 --> 00:14:29,990
像你这样口风紧的人  我们用得上
We could use someone who says as little as you do.

241
00:15:38,690 --> 00:15:39,570
丽萨
Lisa!

242
00:15:46,830 --> 00:15:49,740
-我一直在找她  -我不知道她在哪
- I've been looking for her. - I have no idea where she is.

243
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,730
-我帮你拿吧  -不用了
- Let me help you with that. - No. No, I'm okay.

244
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:58,560
-我很乐意帮你拿  -你吓到我了
- I'm happy to carry it for you. - You're scaring me.

245
00:16:00,110 --> 00:16:02,220
我只是担心她而已
I'm just worried about her. That's all.

246
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:04,360
我戒了
I'm clean.

247
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:07,000
很好
Good.

248
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:10,160
至少我努力在戒  求你别缠着我了
At least I'm trying to get clean. Please leave me alone.

249
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,350
就是
Just...

250
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,140
如果你有瑞秋的消息  请你
If you hear from Rachel, just, uh...

251
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,290
告诉她我全都打点好了
tell her I've taken care of everything.

252
00:16:29,410 --> 00:16:31,460
她可以回来了  不会有事的
She can come home and everything will be fine.

253
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:39,890
我想她  你知道吗
I miss her, you know?

254
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:48,380
抱歉
I'm sorry.

255
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,600
你不接吗
You going to answer that?

256
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,370
我说得对吗
So, was I right?

257
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:25,160
你的电话响了
Your phone is ringing.

258
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:36,330
你按边上的按钮就可以直接挂断
You know, you can just hang it up by pressing the button on the side.

259
00:17:36,340 --> 00:17:39,110
-你不用拒接  -我习惯了
- You don't have to decline-- - I'm a creature of habit.

260
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:43,320
是的  你是对的
So, yeah, you were right.

261
00:17:43,710 --> 00:17:47,170
这部电话只用过一次  拨打了一个号码
This phone has only been used once to call one number, once.

262
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:50,250
我用了生产序列号
I mean, I used the manufacturer's serial number

263
00:17:50,260 --> 00:17:51,690
追踪到了它的经销商所在地
and tracked down where it's distributed to.

264
00:17:51,690 --> 00:17:54,600
是在  杜邦环岛的一家商店
It was a, um... A shop in Dupont Circle.

265
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,060
打给了谁
And who did it call?

266
00:17:56,530 --> 00:17:57,840
查无此人
Comes up unknown.

267
00:17:58,300 --> 00:17:59,630
不过前几位数字
But the prefix...

268
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:02,360
听着  你得找警察或联调局谈
And, look, you're gonna have to talk to the police or the FBI.

269
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:04,310
-我不能一直  -别担心  我担着
- I just can't keep-- - Don't worry. It's on me.

270
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:08,560
那个号码的前几位  我看着像政府号码
The prefix on the call, it looks like a government number to me.

271
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:12,840
喂
Hello.

272
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:18,310
他跟踪你了  什么时候
He followed you? When?

273
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:20,480
-我得去  -好的
- I've got to... - Yeah.

274
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:24,750
好的  如果你觉得现在待的地方安全  
Okay. Okay, if you feel safe where you are,

275
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:26,140
那就待着  我来找你
stay there. I'm coming to you.

276
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:34,130
有什么不能在电话上告诉我的
So what couldn't you tell me over the phone?

277
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:36,280
杰姬·夏普
Jackie Sharp.

278
00:18:37,030 --> 00:18:38,080
她怎么了
What about her?

279
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:41,180
你真不知道吗
You really don't know?

280
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,790
我还以为这事是白宫传出来的
I thought this was coming out of the White House.

281
00:18:46,180 --> 00:18:46,900
马上要爆出来了
The story's about to break

282
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:49,990
说她拿立法换取竞选资金
that she traded legislation for campaign funds.

283
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:51,660
消息来源呢
The source?

284
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:54,590
所以是未经确认的
So, unconfirmed.

285
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:57,150
一小时内就会上《德拉吉报道》了
It's going to be on Drudge within the hour.

286
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,960
你真没什么要说的吗
You really don't have anything to say?

287
00:19:02,310 --> 00:19:04,870
如果是真的  很遗憾看到民主党
If it's true, it's just sad to see the unexpected fall

288
00:19:04,870 --> 00:19:06,590
一颗曾经的新星这样出人意料地陨落
of a once rising star in the Democratic Party.

289
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:07,730
得了吧
Stop it.

290
00:19:08,970 --> 00:19:10,940
夏普本能让委员会拿下一分
Sharp would've been a get for the committee.

291
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:17,090
如果你仍愿意作证  我们就仍愿意谈
If you're still willing to appear, we're still willing to talk.

292
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:22,130
回见
See ya.

293
00:19:28,050 --> 00:19:30,970
{\pos(200.7,140.4)}"易援"女士

294
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,930
我们这个政府不是这么办事的
This is not how we do things in this administration.

295
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,690
你希望她不作证
You wanted her not to testify.

296
00:19:35,860 --> 00:19:37,990
现在罗梅洛不可能逼她就范了
And there's no way Romero can force her to now.

297
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:42,000
你让我的新闻发言人
You've put my press secretary

298
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,450
和他的人处于了非常尴尬的境地
and his staff in a very difficult situation.

299
00:19:44,450 --> 00:19:46,730
有人泄密  并不是你
It was a leak, and it didn't come from you.

300
00:19:47,230 --> 00:19:49,190
我真心觉得这样才能占得先机
I really felt this was the way to get ahead of it.

301
00:19:49,190 --> 00:19:50,340
这叫占得先机
This is getting ahead of it?

302
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:51,290
我向你们保证  她的律师
I guarantee you her lawyers

303
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:53,330
现在一定让她保持沉默  缄口不谈
tell her to plead the Fifth now, across the board.

304
00:19:53,340 --> 00:19:55,160
最重要的是  对涉及你们的事闭嘴
Most importantly, where it concerns you.

305
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,740
但这都是在我跟佩特罗夫谈判时发生的
But all of this happened while I was negotiating with Petrov.

306
00:19:57,740 --> 00:19:59,650
对大众而言  你当时是第一夫人
Oh, to the public, you were the First Lady,

307
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:01,520
正不眠不休地守在丈夫的床边
sitting vigil by your husband's bed.

308
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:04,350
所以这都是在唐纳德·布莱斯的监管下发生的
So, actually, all of this happened under Donald Blythe's watch.

309
00:20:05,910 --> 00:20:07,890
如果你们觉得我越界了  很抱歉
I'm sorry if you think I overstepped.

310
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:10,630
我是想保护你们
I was trying to protect you.

311
00:20:19,210 --> 00:20:20,490
他做了正确的事
He did the right thing.

312
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:22,720
我不介意他做了什么
Oh, I don't mind what he did.

313
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:24,580
我介意的是他做事的方式
I mind the way he did it.

314
00:20:26,470 --> 00:20:28,370
-莉安  -副总统女士
- LeAnn... - Madam Vice President.

315
00:20:28,370 --> 00:20:30,280
抱歉  我的行程太满了
I'm sorry my schedule is so full.

316
00:20:30,290 --> 00:20:31,470
没关系  我非常理解
No, I completely understand,

317
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:33,050
毕竟你要处理那么多事
with everything that you're dealing with.

318
00:20:33,050 --> 00:20:34,950
抱歉我这么固执
I'm sorry for being so insistent,

319
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:35,710
但我觉得应该让你知道
but I thought you should

320
00:20:35,710 --> 00:20:37,660
简·戴维斯昨天来找我了
know that Jane Davis came after me yesterday.

321
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:38,870
找你
Came after you?

322
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:41,380
她想让我去为她工作  不知你是否知情
She wanted me to work for her. I didn't know if you knew.

323
00:20:41,690 --> 00:20:42,980
为她做哪方面的工作
In what capacity?

324
00:20:43,610 --> 00:20:46,020
这点我还不确定  不过
That, I'm not clear on, but it...

325
00:20:46,020 --> 00:20:48,740
她想要关于艾丹·麦卡伦的信息
She wanted information about Aidan Macallan.

326
00:20:48,740 --> 00:20:50,770
希望你知道我绝不会透漏一个字
I hope you know I would never say a word.

327
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:54,040
谢谢你让我知道这些
Thank you for bringing this to my attention.

328
00:20:55,740 --> 00:20:58,510
女士  我希望能讨论一下我的前途
Ma'am, I was hoping we could discuss my future.

329
00:20:58,750 --> 00:21:02,140
莉安  我很乐意讨论你的前途  但现在不行
Oh, LeAnn, I would love to discuss your future, but not yet.

330
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:06,810
如果你愿意  女士  艾丹的事我能帮忙
If you would like, ma'am, I can help with Aidan.

331
00:21:06,970 --> 00:21:08,600
你尽管吩咐
Anything that's required.

332
00:21:09,020 --> 00:21:10,180
很高兴知道你有这个心
That's good to know.

333
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:32,910
你觉得莉安·哈维不会告诉我吗
Did you think LeAnn Harvey wouldn't tell me?

334
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:35,990
我从不假设人们会做什么或不会做什么
I never assume what people will do or won't do.

335
00:21:35,990 --> 00:21:39,120
-我以为我们在默契合作  -没错啊
- I thought we were working well together. - We are.

336
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:41,770
绕过我套取信息
Well, going around me to get information

337
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,270
只会在你我之间造成嫌隙
will only create discord between us.

338
00:21:44,730 --> 00:21:46,650
我并不想这样  克莱尔
I wouldn't want that, Claire.

339
00:21:47,670 --> 00:21:49,670
-戴维斯女士  -总统先生
- Miss Davis. - Mr. President.

340
00:21:49,670 --> 00:21:50,860
抱歉我来晚了
I'm sorry I'm late.

341
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:52,870
副总统告诉我你的联系人
The vice president has told me that your contacts

342
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:55,540
再次跟丢了艾哈迈迪
have once again lost track of Ahmadi.

343
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:57,100
是  我解释过
Yes, as I explained,

344
00:21:57,100 --> 00:22:00,330
叙利亚局势每天都在天翻地覆
Syria is like a different country one day to the next.

345
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:02,580
这你得归咎于维克多·佩特罗夫
Yes, well, you can thank Viktor Petrov for that.

346
00:22:02,580 --> 00:22:03,960
我是怪他
Oh, I do.

347
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:07,690
夫人
Ma'am?

348
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:10,080
我得失陪了  简
Oh, you'll have to excuse me, Jane.

349
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:12,240
我现在都快忙疯了
The schedule is crazy these days.

350
00:22:12,240 --> 00:22:13,400
当然
Oh, of course.

351
00:22:15,780 --> 00:22:17,900
有没有搞错  国务院加国防部
Really? The State Department, the Pentagon,

352
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,700
连个艾哈迈迪都捉不住
we can't get close to Ahmadi?

353
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,230
我只想要和平
I just want peace.

354
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:24,320
是啊  和平的利润最丰厚
Yes, there's nothing that makes profits like peace.

355
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:27,360
而有利润的地方最和平
And nothing makes peace like profits.

356
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:31,750
总统先生  我能有话直说[迟钝]吗
Mr. President, may I be blunt?

357
00:22:32,150 --> 00:22:34,910
我可不觉得你是迟钝的人  戴维斯女士
Well, I would never accuse you of dullness, Miss Davis.

358
00:22:37,950 --> 00:22:42,030
霍姆斯城将会遭受一场毒气袭击
There's going to be a gas attack happening in the city of Homs.

359
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:46,750
而如果说  您划下红线
If you were to, let us say, draw a line in the sand...

360
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,950
然后又发生了这样惨烈的袭击
and if this tragic attack were to happen...

361
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,730
那美国政府将不得不
the US government would have

362
00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:56,760
加派三万多名士兵进驻
to send in an additional 30,000 or so soldiers.

363
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:59,330
以保护石油管线
To protect the oil lines,

364
00:22:59,330 --> 00:23:02,510
阻止佩特罗夫拿下大马士革
to keep Petrov from getting into Damascus.

365
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:05,530
当然了  还要保护人民
And, of course, to protect the people.

366
00:23:07,610 --> 00:23:11,410
这么大规模的军队几乎就是全面占领了
That's venturing close to occupation with those kind of numbers.

367
00:23:11,580 --> 00:23:15,610
我只是在说  也许宣战委员会
All I'm saying is maybe the Declaration of War Committee

368
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:18,640
终于可以辩论他们该辩论的了
could finally debate what they were mandated to.

369
00:23:19,420 --> 00:23:20,480
开战
A war.

370
00:23:26,990 --> 00:23:28,930
你认识马克·厄舍吗
Do you know Mark Usher?

371
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:35,570
认识  我们合作过
Yes, we worked together.

372
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,350
当时他在协助一位众议员
He was handling a congressman.

373
00:23:39,130 --> 00:23:40,080
马克
Mark.

374
00:23:42,030 --> 00:23:43,460
有人给你拿过什么吗
Has anyone offered you anything?

375
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:44,980
没有  不用  谢谢了
Oh, no, I'm good. Thanks.

376
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,890
你和简·戴维斯合作过吗
Have you ever worked with Jane Davis?

377
00:23:59,490 --> 00:24:01,940
戴维斯是她继父的姓
Davis is the stepfather's name.

378
00:24:03,070 --> 00:24:04,370
一个只干了一任的参议员
A one-term senator.

379
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,250
总之
Uh, anyway, yeah,

380
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:10,160
她曾对我的一位客户有点兴趣
she was interested in a client I had, at some point.

381
00:24:11,460 --> 00:24:12,990
国会议员候选人
A candidate for Congress.

382
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:16,880
可怜人  厄舍一意识到他不够强硬
Poor guy. The minute Usher realized he wasn't formidable enough,

383
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,060
就甩手走人  让他自生自灭了
he just dumped him. Let him go.

384
00:24:20,150 --> 00:24:21,390
但马克就这样
But that's Mark.

385
00:24:22,450 --> 00:24:24,130
他擅长发现人才
He has an eye for talent.

386
00:24:24,550 --> 00:24:27,720
喜欢密切关注你  而他自己却站得远远的
Likes to keep you close while he keeps himself remote.

387
00:24:28,180 --> 00:24:31,560
但是他不同意她在一些问题上的立场
But he disagreed with some of her positions,

388
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,650
于是资金就断掉了
the money went away.

389
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:37,410
听我说  千万别让简骗了你
Listen, don't let Jane fool you.

390
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:42,260
她看上去可能有点  没有章法
She can seem a bit... haphazard...

391
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:44,030
但只要他利用完了你
But once he's done with you...

392
00:24:45,490 --> 00:24:48,800
就会像关上开关那么干脆决绝
it's as if a switch gets turned off.

393
00:24:49,040 --> 00:24:50,800
但她冷酷无情
But she is merciless.

394
00:24:52,710 --> 00:24:55,150
要多专一就有多专一
Single-minded as a single mind can be.

395
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,950
怎么了  我今天忘了吃饭了
What? Forgot to eat today.

396
00:25:17,220 --> 00:25:18,510
你给我查出什么了
What have you got for me?

397
00:25:21,030 --> 00:25:23,920
-不知道  -少跟我"不知道"
- I don't know. - Don't do "I don't know."

398
00:25:26,030 --> 00:25:27,310
我去见了梅瑞迪斯·李
Saw Meredith Lee.

399
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:33,100
我提到了莫雷蒂基金  器官移植
I mentioned the Moretti Fund, organ transplants, uh...

400
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:36,080
她看起来有点紧张  可是  我说不好
She got a little tense, but... I don't know.

401
00:25:37,550 --> 00:25:39,280
你怎么没告诉我你被开除了
Why didn't you tell me you were fired?

402
00:25:39,290 --> 00:25:42,060
-原来是你  -就是我和你女友说了话
- Oh, that was you? - Who talked to your girlfriend? Yeah.

403
00:25:42,750 --> 00:25:43,750
多久了
How long?

404
00:25:44,810 --> 00:25:47,200
有什么区别  我穷途末路了
What's the difference? I'm tapped.

405
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:50,470
我们在干什么呢
What are we doing here?

406
00:25:50,470 --> 00:25:52,370
我不喜欢有人在我车上吃东西
I don't like eating in my car.

407
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,420
我觉得劳拉·莫雷蒂的丈夫
I think Laura Moretti's husband

408
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:57,810
在捐赠名单上被插队了
was jumped on the donor list.

409
00:25:59,740 --> 00:26:02,000
-这你是从哪听说的  -直觉
- Where the hell did you get that? - My gut.

410
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,240
不信我分析给你听
I can lay it out for you.

411
00:26:04,340 --> 00:26:06,420
敢这么说话  你最好说到做到
Yeah, you say something like that, you better.

412
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:11,340
沙林毒气  主要袭击霍姆斯近郊的平民区
Sarin gas. Mostly against civilians in suburban areas of Homs.

413
00:26:11,340 --> 00:26:14,170
-我们在和一帮畜生斗  -太可怕了
- We're dealing with animals here. - It's horrifying.

414
00:26:14,170 --> 00:26:17,010
你知道我过去一直在尽量克制  但是
Now, you know I've always shown restraint in the past, but...

415
00:26:17,010 --> 00:26:21,430
我打算发布行政命令  部署军事行动了
I'm going to be making an executive order for military action.

416
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:24,490
先空袭  然后地面部队进驻
Air strikes followed by ground troops.

417
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:26,480
你得向联合国提交报告
You'll need to present to the UN.

418
00:26:27,230 --> 00:26:29,470
这个情报是哪来的
Where is this intelligence coming from?

419
00:26:29,470 --> 00:26:31,340
简报里都写了
Well, it's all there in the briefing.

420
00:26:31,870 --> 00:26:34,130
但既然我们知道这事会发生
But if we know this is going to happen,

421
00:26:34,130 --> 00:26:37,880
我们为什么不提前制止呢
well, then why aren't we stopping it before it does?

422
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:45,550
弗兰西斯还留着你的辞职信
Francis held on to your resignation letter.

423
00:26:46,710 --> 00:26:49,300
他想把它撕掉
And he wants to tear it up.

424
00:26:56,410 --> 00:27:00,880
我知道这几个月来你多么艰辛
I know how difficult these past few months have been for you.

425
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,610
我们要求你做了很多
We've really asked a lot.

426
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:05,380
但等我们部署了军事行动
But once we're on the other side of this military action,

427
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:09,740
我们会准许你如愿离开政府
you have our blessing to leave the administration if you choose.

428
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:12,630
但当然  我们更希望你留下
But, of course, we'd prefer if you stay on.

429
00:27:13,390 --> 00:27:15,300
希望这是不言自明的
Hope that goes without saying.

430
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:22,360
对平民使用
Using weapons of mass destruction

431
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,510
大规模杀伤性武器是战争罪
against civilians is a war crime.

432
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:28,070
我很感激有机会能完成此事
I appreciate the opportunity to see this through to the end.

433
00:27:28,250 --> 00:27:30,150
我们就希望你会这么说
We were hoping you would say that.

434
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:31,450
谢谢你  凯茜
Thank you, Cathy.

435
00:27:31,460 --> 00:27:32,990
谢谢  总统先生
Thank you, Mr. President.

436
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:39,840
你担心她吗
Are you worried about her?

437
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,790
我们得开始想
We need to start thinking about

438
00:27:42,790 --> 00:27:45,140
我们身边的人了
the people we surround ourselves with.

439
00:27:45,800 --> 00:27:48,270
这让我想到了汤姆
Which has made me think of Tom...

440
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:54,000
他现在已经没理由留在这里了  是吧
who doesn't really have a reason to be here anymore, does he?

441
00:27:56,230 --> 00:27:57,530
没有正式理由
Not an official one, no,

442
00:27:57,530 --> 00:28:00,780
但我想或许我们可以给他个顾问之名
but I thought maybe we could bring him on as a consultant.

443
00:28:11,670 --> 00:28:13,870
当然  这取决于你
Well, of course, that's entirely up to you.

444
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,860
只是一天的时间和精力有限
There's just only so much time and energy in a single day,

445
00:28:17,860 --> 00:28:20,490
我觉得我们该不断自省
and I think we need to constantly be asking ourselves,

446
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:23,600
"我是否尽可能明智地利用我的时间和精力了"
"Am I spending it as wisely as I can?"

447
00:28:36,530 --> 00:28:38,520
-谢谢  -简  真抱歉
- Thank you. - Jane, I'm so sorry

448
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:40,060
-从派对上把你叫走  -没事
- to pull you away from your party. - No, no, no.

449
00:28:40,070 --> 00:28:42,770
-当我在电话上听到你的声音  -我就是
- When I heard your voice on the phone... - I just... I just...

450
00:28:42,770 --> 00:28:45,890
-我不知道该怎么办  -出什么事了吗
- I don't know what to do. - Did something happen?

451
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:47,400
安德伍德夫妇在计划
The Underwoods are planning

452
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,530
对霍姆斯进行空袭  增派军队
air strikes and a troop surge in Homs.

453
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:55,090
-太可怕了  -你了解这事吗
- How awful. - Do you know anything about this?

454
00:28:57,410 --> 00:29:00,740
佩特罗夫把那里变成了地狱
Petrov is making the whole region a disaster.

455
00:29:01,050 --> 00:29:04,710
没有哪个卷入中东局势的人能得到好处
No one who ever got tangled up in the Middle East came out ahead.

456
00:29:04,710 --> 00:29:06,970
随佩特罗夫去吧
Let Petrov own it.

457
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:14,520
有可怕的事将要发生
There's something terrible that is going to happen...

458
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:16,290
我们可以阻止
that we can prevent.

459
00:29:16,500 --> 00:29:17,350
这样啊
I see.

460
00:29:18,010 --> 00:29:21,040
我要向联合国提交我方红线警告
I'm scheduled to present some kind of red line at the UN.

461
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:23,550
-但我们还可以退一步的  -我要怎么帮忙
- But we can still pull back. - How can I help?

462
00:29:24,380 --> 00:29:27,670
跟总统和副总统谈谈
Talk to the president, the vice president.

463
00:29:29,710 --> 00:29:30,520
我会的
I will.

464
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:36,180
他们真可怕  是吧
They're terrible, terrible people, aren't they?

465
00:29:40,710 --> 00:29:41,620
简
Jane...

466
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:45,100
对他们一定要小心
be very careful with them.

467
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:48,600
当然
Of course.

468
00:29:51,220 --> 00:29:52,740
这是老友的忠告
That's from an old friend.

469
00:29:55,670 --> 00:29:57,120
我们还是朋友吧
Are we still friends?

470
00:29:58,500 --> 00:29:59,540
当然
Of course.

471
00:30:21,010 --> 00:30:22,770
他说总统接受的肝脏
He says the liver the president received

472
00:30:22,770 --> 00:30:26,020
本该是给一个叫安东尼·莫雷蒂的人的
was supposed to go to a man named Anthony Moretti.

473
00:30:26,290 --> 00:30:28,190
他说道格逼迫
And he says that Doug forced

474
00:30:28,190 --> 00:30:30,390
当时的卫生和人类服务部部长
then Secretary of Health and Human Services

475
00:30:30,390 --> 00:30:31,610
把总统排在名单最前
to put the president at the top of the list,

476
00:30:31,610 --> 00:30:33,890
结果莫雷蒂因此死了
which resulted in Moretti's death.

477
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:39,110
道格还跟他的遗孀发生了关系
Oh, and Doug also has become involved with the man's widow.

478
00:30:40,130 --> 00:30:41,210
干得漂亮
That's a nice touch.

479
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:44,560
他有证据吗
And does... does he have proof?

480
00:30:44,650 --> 00:30:47,080
关于恋情吗  这个简单
About the relationship? It's easy to prove that.

481
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,220
名单的话  他知道梅瑞迪斯·李有所隐瞒
But the list, he knows that Meredith Lee is hiding something.

482
00:30:50,220 --> 00:30:52,690
他打算再去找她谈
And he's ready to go back and talk to her about it.

483
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:54,830
你信任他吗
Do you trust him?

484
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:57,970
我不知道他干吗要编造这些
I don't know why he'd make any of this up.

485
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:00,250
我在外面
Hey, I'm outside.

486
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,300
你玩得开心吗
Did you have a good time?

487
00:31:10,140 --> 00:31:12,140
我在这种场合已经开心不了了
I never do at those things anymore.

488
00:31:12,970 --> 00:31:14,360
必要之恶
Necessary evils.

489
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,580
不像以前了
It's not like the old days,

490
00:31:15,580 --> 00:31:17,870
你还能结识出人意料的人
when you used to meet surprising people.

491
00:31:19,900 --> 00:31:21,040
是人们不那么出人意料了
Did people get less surprising

492
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:23,040
还是我们不容易被打动了
or are we less easily surprised?

493
00:31:25,120 --> 00:31:26,730
是啊
Well, exactly.

494
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:29,490
-我的车来了  -她跟我问了你
- This is me. - She asked me about you.

495
00:31:31,820 --> 00:31:34,580
-我猜到了  你怎么说的  -你...
- I figured. What'd you say? - That you're...

496
00:31:36,650 --> 00:31:39,720
强大  什么的
formidable, etcetera.

497
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:45,360
我也这么跟他说你的  什么的
Yeah, I told him the same about you, etcetera.

498
00:31:47,450 --> 00:31:48,770
他可以当个伟大的总统
He could be a great president.

499
00:31:51,820 --> 00:31:53,220
但他想做吗
But does he want to be?

500
00:31:53,250 --> 00:31:55,450
而且什么算伟大
And what is great?

501
00:31:57,880 --> 00:31:59,170
还有她
And then there's her.

502
00:32:00,780 --> 00:32:02,010
她怎么样
What about her?

503
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:04,550
她怎么了
What about her?

504
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:15,080
如果鲍勃或泰瑞是副主席
Because if Bob or Terry were the ranking member,

505
00:32:15,080 --> 00:32:16,380
我就找他们了
I'd be talking to them.

506
00:32:17,250 --> 00:32:19,940
我要罗梅洛做光杆司令
I want Romero's clerk stripped.

507
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:23,460
对  他给委员会成员的任何预算
Yeah, whatever budget he's got for his seat on that committee.

508
00:32:23,460 --> 00:32:27,100
不不  我这是为了党派
No, no, I'm asking for the sake of the party.

509
00:32:27,670 --> 00:32:30,650
杰姬·夏普的事我们躲过一劫  但这事没完
Look, we survived Jackie Sharp, but it's not gonna end there.

510
00:32:31,180 --> 00:32:33,150
事实上  我在因为
The truth is I'm being punished

511
00:32:33,150 --> 00:32:36,730
为我们选民最在乎的事抗争而受惩罚
for fighting for the issues that our base cares most about.

512
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,780
对  谢谢
Yes, and thank you.

513
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:45,520
道尔说几乎查不到厄舍的任何料
Doyle says there's almost nothing on Usher.

514
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:48,330
他喜欢赌博  一般能赢
He likes to gamble, usually wins.

515
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:52,270
但问题是  道尔找过马歇尔
But here's the thing... Doyle spoke with Marshall,

516
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:54,990
我们知道他离开康威团队时并不愉快
who we know did not have a happy exit from the Conway campaign.

517
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:58,600
他说  厄舍加入我们政府前
Now, he said that before Usher joined our administration,

518
00:32:58,810 --> 00:33:01,220
他还打算培养罗梅洛竞选总统
he was grooming Romero for a presidential run.

519
00:33:03,270 --> 00:33:05,470
先生  我认为他在两头讨好
Sir, I believe he's playing both sides

520
00:33:05,470 --> 00:33:07,320
这个委员会的目标
of whatever this committee is after.

521
00:33:09,670 --> 00:33:11,590
我不是民主党人  杰弗里
I'm not a Democrat, Jeffrey.

522
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:14,870
我还是共和党  只是碰巧在白宫工作
I'm still a Republican, just happen to work for the White House.

523
00:33:14,870 --> 00:33:18,000
我是说  趁现在还行  控制下艾力克斯
All I'm saying is let's rein Alex in while we still can.

524
00:33:18,830 --> 00:33:20,140
等他把自己的党派搅翻了天
'Cause after he rips through his own party,

525
00:33:20,140 --> 00:33:21,690
就会去折腾我们党了  不是吗
he'll come after ours, wouldn't you think?

526
00:33:22,650 --> 00:33:23,830
杰弗  你是主席
Yeah, and Jeff, you're the chair...

527
00:33:23,830 --> 00:33:25,530
不  什么  不  听我说
No... What? No, listen.

528
00:33:25,610 --> 00:33:27,930
等等  等等
Wait. Wait! Wait.

529
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,550
你欠我的  我们都知道
And you owe me, and we both know it,

530
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:33,690
这种事我不会大声说出来
and that's not the kind of thing I like to say out loud.

531
00:33:33,780 --> 00:33:34,710
什么
What is?

532
00:33:37,060 --> 00:33:38,180
什么时候的事
When did that happen?

533
00:33:41,430 --> 00:33:42,340
确认了吗
Confirmed?

534
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,100
嗯
Yeah?

535
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:52,480
好吧
Yes, well...

536
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:55,880
沃克要作证
just because Walker's gonna take the stand,

537
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:57,910
不代表他会说什么  是吧
doesn't mean he'll say anything. Right?

538
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:13,160
你今早对我说的那个词是什么
What was that word you said to me this morning?

539
00:34:14,190 --> 00:34:15,910
就是现在没人用了的那个
The one no one uses anymore?

540
00:34:16,940 --> 00:34:18,160
黄昏的
Crepuscular.

541
00:34:18,980 --> 00:34:19,780
对了
Right.

542
00:34:24,370 --> 00:34:28,100
一些我最喜欢的动物就是晨昏性的
Some of my favorite animals are crepuscular.

543
00:34:30,390 --> 00:34:31,160
喂
Yes.

544
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,330
什么
What?

545
00:34:34,630 --> 00:34:35,380
什么时候
When?

546
00:34:36,530 --> 00:34:39,030
天呐  该死
Jesus! God damn it!

547
00:34:46,580 --> 00:34:47,380
克莱尔
Claire!

548
00:34:48,870 --> 00:34:51,050
-克莱尔  -我在厨房
- Claire! - I'm in the kitchen.

549
00:34:52,570 --> 00:34:53,920
沃克要作证
Walker's gonna testify.

550
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,580
-什么时候  -最早下周
- When? - Early as next week.

551
00:34:57,640 --> 00:34:59,720
他会说他跟汉默施密特说的那些话
He's gonna say the same thing he said to Hammerschmidt.

552
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:01,020
不会有新伤害
There's not gonna be any new damage.

553
00:35:01,030 --> 00:35:03,300
-我们不能确定  -我们去找厄舍
- We don't know that for sure. - Let's get Usher.

554
00:35:03,300 --> 00:35:05,080
我早上肯定要找他
You bet I'm gonna talk to him in the morning.

555
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:06,150
你去哪
Where are you going?

556
00:35:06,150 --> 00:35:08,900
在这房子里找块空荡的地方
To get some goddamn space in this house!

557
00:35:25,460 --> 00:35:28,670
我可以解决沃克  我们给他开条件
I can take care of Walker. We'll make him an offer.

558
00:35:29,540 --> 00:35:30,910
让他回到政坛
A place back on the stage,

559
00:35:30,980 --> 00:35:33,050
去哪个资金雄厚的大学当校长  他会接受的
chancellor of some well-endowed university. He'll take it.

560
00:35:33,050 --> 00:35:34,260
他可能会  但首先
He just might. But first,

561
00:35:34,260 --> 00:35:36,450
我要知道你有罗梅洛什么料
I want to know what you have on Romero.

562
00:35:36,810 --> 00:35:37,970
完全没有
I don't have a thing.

563
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:40,750
-得了  -道格  别失礼
- Please. - Doug, let's not be rude.

564
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:42,790
这我难以相信
I find that impossible to believe.

565
00:35:42,790 --> 00:35:44,040
如果我知道  你会知道的
If I did, you would know it.

566
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,840
你和我都是老手了
You and I have been at this a long time.

567
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:48,650
你愿考虑一个候选人都肯定先审查过他
You wouldn't even consider a candidate without vetting him first.

568
00:35:48,650 --> 00:35:49,790
我觉得艾力克斯很有前途
I thought Alex had a future.

569
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:51,920
是啊  就我所知可以竞选总统
Yeah, a run for the presidency as I understand it.

570
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,350
他像上浆的白衬衫一样干净
He's clean and crisp as a starched white shirt.

571
00:35:54,350 --> 00:35:55,640
你得做出决定  马克
You're gonna have to make a decision, Mark.

572
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:57,720
是为我和克莱尔工作  还是怎么
You wanna work for me and Claire, or not?

573
00:35:57,730 --> 00:36:01,450
我已经联络了我自己党派的人
I have already reached out to members of my own party.

574
00:36:01,450 --> 00:36:03,850
我为帮助你动用了我的政治资本
I've used my political capital to help you.

575
00:36:03,850 --> 00:36:05,310
但你还是没回答我的问题
But you're still not answering my question.

576
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:06,450
我已经回答了
I think I have.

577
00:36:07,610 --> 00:36:10,340
我不需要让你或安德伍德夫人相信我的价值
And I don't need to convince you or Mrs. Underwood of my worth.

578
00:36:20,580 --> 00:36:21,810
认识您很荣幸
It's an honor to meet you.

579
00:36:23,260 --> 00:36:26,350
赛斯  杰弗瑞斯先生稍后会去找你
Seth, Mr. Jeffries will catch up with you momentarily.

580
00:36:29,950 --> 00:36:31,600
我得长话短说了
I'm going to keep this brief.

581
00:36:35,330 --> 00:36:36,920
如果你的说法是真的
If what you're saying is true...

582
00:36:37,830 --> 00:36:40,380
道格·斯坦普救了我丈夫一命
Doug Stamper saved my husband's life.

583
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:41,840
是的
He did.

584
00:36:42,730 --> 00:36:45,130
还因此害死了别人
And he also cost someone else his.

585
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:51,700
我猜你是那种有很多欲求的人
Well, I suspect you're the kind of man that wants many things.

586
00:36:52,570 --> 00:36:54,200
但你犯了个错误
But you have made a mistake.

587
00:36:55,690 --> 00:36:59,590
职业上讲  我只有一样一直渴求的东西
There's only one thing, professionally, that I've always wanted.

588
00:37:00,740 --> 00:37:02,210
就是进白宫工作
It's to work in the White House.

589
00:37:03,740 --> 00:37:05,020
赛斯会送你出去
Seth will see you out.

590
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,170
抱歉刚刚不得不走开
Sorry for the interruption.

591
00:37:14,060 --> 00:37:14,990
你说到哪了
You were saying...

592
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:21,370
凯茜一直是个好人
Cathy was always a very good person.

593
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:24,040
她内心是的  她有良心
At her core, she has a core.

594
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,100
保佑她
Bless her.

595
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:30,170
霍姆斯的事对她可能太为难
This whole Homs initiative might be too difficult for her.

596
00:37:33,270 --> 00:37:37,400
你让人很难读懂
You know... you're very hard to read.

597
00:37:38,730 --> 00:37:39,860
这也合理
Which makes sense.

598
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:44,630
这几年来  你一直左右逢源
For the last several years, you've been a familiar face.

599
00:37:46,490 --> 00:37:47,950
一定很累人
Must get exhausting.

600
00:37:48,610 --> 00:37:51,860
你能跟他一起欢笑的人都很少吧
Must be hardly any people you can even share a laugh with.

601
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:02,130
你该想想该怎么好好利用我
You should figure out how to take full advantage of me.

602
00:38:03,970 --> 00:38:05,770
我可以帮你如愿
I can help you get what you want.

603
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:09,350
如果你告诉我你的愿望
If you tell me what it is.

604
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:11,050
我喜欢帮助他人
I enjoy helping others.

605
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:14,100
我觉得你知道我的愿望
I think you know what I want.

606
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:14,960
是啊
Yes...

607
00:38:16,150 --> 00:38:18,570
但你是现在想要  还是四年后要
But do you want it now or in four years?

608
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:28,880
我要全世界看到艾哈迈迪被逮捕
I want the whole world to see Ahmadi's capture...

609
00:38:29,690 --> 00:38:32,860
铺天盖地的报道
on every news outlet and every screen.

610
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:36,840
为了党派利益  我更希望沃克先生不要作证
For the good of the party, I'd prefer Mr. Walker not testify.

611
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:39,930
我在考虑离开宣战委员会
I'm considering taking myself off the Declaration of War Committee.

612
00:38:39,930 --> 00:38:41,130
艾力克斯  你不用那么做
Alex, you don't have to do that.

613
00:38:41,130 --> 00:38:43,320
你可以随意怎么处置它
And you can do what you will with it.

614
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:47,480
但条件是总统要做正确的事
But that's conditional on the president doing the right thing.

615
00:38:49,140 --> 00:38:50,080
是什么
And what is that?

616
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:51,660
辞职
Resigning.

617
00:38:52,020 --> 00:38:54,290
再说一遍  我只是为党派考虑
Again, I'm only thinking of the party.

618
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,650
嗯
Yeah...

619
00:39:03,490 --> 00:39:05,810
你他妈以为你是谁啊
Who the fuck do you think you are?

620
00:39:06,370 --> 00:39:08,460
-别对我说粗话  -闭上臭嘴
- Oh, don't use that language with me... - Shut the fuck up.

621
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:12,580
你根本不知道你在做什么
You have no idea, none, about what you're doing.

622
00:39:12,580 --> 00:39:13,410
请你离开我的办公室
I'd like you to leave my office.

623
00:39:13,410 --> 00:39:14,750
你给我听好
Now you listen carefully to me.

624
00:39:14,750 --> 00:39:16,490
-我说  -闭嘴  艾力克斯
- I said... - Shut up, Alex!

625
00:39:18,340 --> 00:39:19,540
听听这个头条
Here's a headline for you.

626
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:22,080
"艾力克斯·罗梅洛勾结康威州长
"Alex Romero colluded with Governor Conway

627
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:24,070
利用宣战委员会
to use the Declaration of War Committee

628
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,480
帮他赢得大选"
to help him win an election."

629
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:28,340
-没有  -得了  你清楚你做了什么
- No. - Please, you know you did.

630
00:39:29,480 --> 00:39:31,640
-看这多简单  -滚出去
- See how easy that is? - Get out!

631
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:36,780
听证会上只会有你一个人  我刚见过沃克
You're gonna be all alone at your hearing. I just left Walker.

632
00:39:37,060 --> 00:39:39,340
他打算保持沉默  你会出丑的
He's gonna plead the Fifth. You'll look like a fool.

633
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:44,020
你想出头  没人介意
You want to be out front? No one has a problem with that.

634
00:39:44,890 --> 00:39:48,410
他们希望你出头  因为你也会倒得最快
They want you there, because you'll be the first to fall.

635
00:39:51,870 --> 00:39:53,280
"为了党派"
"For the good of the party."

636
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:01,580
做个好梦  议员
Sleep tight, Congressman.

637
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,340
-谁知道威尔的事  -暂时还没人
- Who knows about Will? - No one, not yet.

638
00:40:05,070 --> 00:40:05,940
还有呢
What else?

639
00:40:08,390 --> 00:40:10,210
我现在为什么还要保护你
Why I'm still protecting you at this point...

640
00:40:11,190 --> 00:40:12,620
我自己都不明白
I don't even understand myself.

641
00:40:18,220 --> 00:40:19,760
沃克打算保持沉默
Walker's gonna plead the Fifth.

642
00:40:19,850 --> 00:40:21,660
罗梅洛也不会折腾
And Romero won't rock the boat.

643
00:40:21,660 --> 00:40:23,640
多谢了  马克
Thank you, Mark, I appreciate that.

644
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:26,020
我建议你安排新闻发布会
I would suggest you schedule a press conference

645
00:40:26,020 --> 00:40:27,420
就在听证会之后
for right after the hearing.

646
00:40:27,530 --> 00:40:28,550
好
All right.

647
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:45,900
告诉我你做过的最恶劣的事
Tell me the worst thing you've ever done.

648
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,120
不好选
It's hard to pick.

649
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:53,280
-我说真的  -我也是
- I'm serious. - So am I.

650
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:02,780
假装爱一个我并不爱的人
Pretended to love someone when I didn't.

651
00:41:04,970 --> 00:41:06,460
可以说  那是最糟的
In a way, that was the worst.

652
00:41:13,780 --> 00:41:15,110
那人知道吗
Did the person know?

653
00:41:19,450 --> 00:41:21,020
她假装不知道
She pretended not to know...

654
00:41:22,970 --> 00:41:24,000
但她知道
but she knew.

655
00:41:25,550 --> 00:41:26,990
她很难受
It was awful for her.

656
00:41:30,090 --> 00:41:31,960
但我为那个错误付出了代价
But I paid for that mistake, too.

657
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:36,430
那种事  会伤害一个人
Those types of things, they take a toll.

658
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,830
真是奇妙  有些选择毫无意义
It's strange how some choices mean nothing

659
00:41:41,210 --> 00:41:43,400
也有一些会决定你的余生
and others govern the rest of your life.

660
00:41:46,440 --> 00:41:48,250
我做过一些可怕的事
I've done some terrible things.

661
00:41:51,460 --> 00:41:52,680
你不用告诉我
You don't have to tell me.

662
00:41:55,610 --> 00:41:57,730
弗兰西斯杀了佐伊·巴恩斯
Francis killed Zoe Barnes.

663
00:41:58,960 --> 00:41:59,720
克莱尔
Claire.

664
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:01,610
弗兰西斯杀了彼得
Francis killed Peter.

665
00:42:01,620 --> 00:42:02,520
别说了
Stop.

666
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:04,530
还会再死许多人
And so many more are gonna die.

667
00:42:04,530 --> 00:42:05,610
别说了
Stop.

668
00:42:20,610 --> 00:42:21,910
我不怕你
You don't scare me.

669
00:42:23,490 --> 00:42:24,420
你该怕
I should.

670
00:42:40,470 --> 00:42:41,380
艾丹
Aidan.

671
00:42:41,920 --> 00:42:42,890
我不叫艾丹了
Not anymore.

672
00:42:42,890 --> 00:42:44,250
你怎么到这儿来的
How did you get here?

673
00:42:44,250 --> 00:42:46,520
有扇门开了  我就出来了
A door opened, I walked out.

674
00:42:46,910 --> 00:42:48,220
听着不太对劲
That doesn't sound right.

675
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:51,310
我拿到了签证  和今晚的机票  我只是
I got a visa and a flight tonight. I just...

676
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,490
我只是想最后再来看看你
I just wanted to see you one last time.

677
00:42:54,490 --> 00:42:56,450
等等  谁要送你走
Wait. Who's getting you out?

678
00:42:56,450 --> 00:42:57,740
无所谓了
That doesn't matter.

679
00:42:58,760 --> 00:43:01,790
-你说什么了  -其实什么都没说
- What did you say? - Honestly, nothing.

680
00:43:02,450 --> 00:43:03,840
我们必须和安德伍德夫妇谈谈
We have to talk to the Underwoods.

681
00:43:03,840 --> 00:43:06,730
-还是算了吧  -这根本说不通
- Nah, I don't think so. - This does not make sense.

682
00:43:10,830 --> 00:43:12,770
你总是喜欢开好车
Well, you always liked to drive a nice car.

683
00:43:15,770 --> 00:43:18,810
艾丹  跟我来吧  我来解决
Aidan, come with me. I'll fix this.

684
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:22,180
我还想让你跟我走呢  我也给你备了条出路
You come with me. I've a way for you to get out.

685
00:43:29,070 --> 00:43:30,360
那好吧
Well, all right, then.

686
00:43:40,490 --> 00:43:42,720
等到明天早上再告诉别人你见到了我
Now, don't you tell anybody you saw me until the morning.

687
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:44,860
我为什么还要告诉别人我见到了你
Why would I tell anyone I saw you at all?

688
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:45,970
不是吧
Really?

689
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:49,810
等等
Wait.

690
00:43:57,900 --> 00:43:59,970
-给  拿上这个  -不行
- Here, take this. - No.

691
00:43:59,970 --> 00:44:02,700
拿着  至少上飞机之前要拿着  好吗
Come on. At least until you get on the flight, all right?

692
00:44:07,620 --> 00:44:08,510
我撤了
I'm out.

693
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:42,470
睡不着
Can't sleep?

694
00:44:45,170 --> 00:44:47,650
外面这么冷  你该披上外套
It's freezing out here. You should have a coat on.

695
00:44:47,890 --> 00:44:48,910
我喜欢
I like it.

696
00:44:53,150 --> 00:44:54,600
别去见沃克
Don't meet with Walker.

697
00:44:55,170 --> 00:44:56,720
我觉得这不是个好主意
I think it's a bad idea.

698
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:01,620
这会提醒他  他最好该怎么做
It'll remind him of his best course of action.

699
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:06,200
你错了  我很抱歉  但是你错了
You're wrong. I'm sorry, but you're wrong.

700
00:45:07,580 --> 00:45:09,580
厄舍已经打点好了
Usher has it under control.

701
00:45:18,650 --> 00:45:20,580
你总是想做什么就做什么
You always do what you want.

702
00:45:24,090 --> 00:45:25,560
汤姆不想走
Tom doesn't want to leave.

703
00:45:27,270 --> 00:45:29,140
汤姆没资格选
Tom doesn't get to choose.

704
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:31,730
外面冷  你进去吧
It's cold. You should go in.

705
00:45:40,860 --> 00:45:43,500
能麻烦你把道格·斯坦普过去三年
If you could get me Doug Stamper's addresses

706
00:45:43,500 --> 00:45:44,850
住过的所有地址给我...
for the last three years...

707
00:45:52,500 --> 00:45:54,100
你知道瑞秋和丽萨的照片条
And do you know what happened to the photo strip

708
00:45:54,100 --> 00:45:55,460
去哪了吗
of Rachel and Lisa?

709
00:45:56,240 --> 00:45:57,420
不见了
It's gone.

710
00:45:58,860 --> 00:46:01,430
我们得自己表明我们的立场
We need to lay out our positions ourselves.

711
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:03,910
我已经在去纽约的路上了
I'm already on my way to New York.

712
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,770
我不希望你说或者做什么
I don't want you to say or do anything

713
00:46:05,770 --> 00:46:07,070
让你感到不舒服的事
that makes you feel uncomfortable.

714
00:46:07,070 --> 00:46:10,120
我不会和政府立场相左的  我不希望这样
I won't contradict the administration. That's not my wish.

715
00:46:10,130 --> 00:46:12,120
我们需要划下红线
We need to draw a line in the sand.

716
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:16,100
当然  我还上飞机吗
Yes, of course. Should I get on my flight?

717
00:46:16,110 --> 00:46:19,170
我觉得你最好还是调头回来吧
I think it might be best if you turn around and come back.

718
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:21,010
听你的
Whatever you think.

719
00:46:21,980 --> 00:46:23,770
就让沃克保持沉默吧
We'll let Walker plead the Fifth.

720
00:46:23,770 --> 00:46:26,870
然后我们再碰头协调立场
Then we'll regroup and make sure we're on the same page.

721
00:46:28,860 --> 00:46:31,520
好吧  调头回去吧
Okay. We need to head back.

722
00:46:42,340 --> 00:46:45,880
"当心纠缠不清的联盟"  总统先生
"Beware entangling alliances," Mr. President.

723
00:46:46,700 --> 00:46:48,760
通常都认为这句话出自华盛顿
You know, that quote is often attributed to Washington,

724
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:51,060
但其实是杰斐逊说的
but it was actually Jefferson who said it.

725
00:46:53,020 --> 00:46:54,830
总之我想先来见见你
Anyway, I wanted to catch you before,

726
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:57,090
赶在马克和你的律师来之前
Mark and your lawyer got here.

727
00:46:57,230 --> 00:46:58,310
总统先生
Mr. President.

728
00:46:59,420 --> 00:47:01,620
我知道这对你并不轻松
I know this hasn't been easy for you.

729
00:47:02,930 --> 00:47:06,010
其实一个人的适应能力几乎不可限量
Well, the truth is, one can get used to almost anything.

730
00:47:07,610 --> 00:47:10,470
总之  恭喜你
Well, at any rate, congratulations.

731
00:47:11,070 --> 00:47:12,510
你就要担任国内
You're about to become the chancellor

732
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:14,140
顶尖大学的校长了
of one of our finest universities.

733
00:47:14,140 --> 00:47:16,640
我们为名誉付出的代价高昂
It's a high price we pay for respectability.

734
00:47:18,170 --> 00:47:20,260
总之  我就是来打个招呼
Anyway, I just wanted to say hello.

735
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:23,470
并且感谢你所做的一切
And to thank you for all you're doing.

736
00:47:24,150 --> 00:47:25,430
用不了多久
In not too long,

737
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:27,950
你就会和那些前总统一样
you're going to become one of those ex-presidents

738
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:30,980
你的成就会让大家
whose work will make everyone...

739
00:47:31,850 --> 00:47:33,620
忘记过去
forget the past.

740
00:47:34,520 --> 00:47:37,190
我也曾是美国总统
I was once the President of the United States.

741
00:47:37,570 --> 00:47:38,940
没错  你的确是
Yes, you were.

742
00:47:39,270 --> 00:47:42,520
然后总统之位被你偷走了  弗兰克
You stole the presidency, Frank.

743
00:47:43,510 --> 00:47:44,650
别这么说  加勒特
Now, Garrett...

744
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:46,330
都是好久以前的事了
This is ancient history,

745
00:47:46,330 --> 00:47:48,360
但以现代政治的标准来看
but by modern political standards,

746
00:47:48,560 --> 00:47:50,600
我是以压倒性优势当选的
my election was a landslide.

747
00:47:51,530 --> 00:47:53,250
我原本打算改变这个国家
I was gonna change this country.

748
00:47:54,150 --> 00:47:57,830
但后来  发生了一些事
But then... uh, things happen.

749
00:47:58,060 --> 00:47:59,110
人们说谎
People lie...

750
00:48:00,170 --> 00:48:01,460
为与他们同步你只好也撒谎
You lie to keep up.

751
00:48:02,590 --> 00:48:05,450
你一直以来被称赞的优点
The things that you've been lauded for all your life,

752
00:48:06,030 --> 00:48:09,240
突然都成了致命缺陷
those are suddenly fatal flaws.

753
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:12,550
曾经和你风雨同舟的人
People who've been with you through thick and thin,

754
00:48:12,790 --> 00:48:16,410
你以为永远不会辜负你的人  还是辜负你了
who you thought would never fail you, they fail you.

755
00:48:17,720 --> 00:48:20,750
你会和讨厌的人结成别扭的同盟
You make strange alliances with unsavory people.

756
00:48:22,390 --> 00:48:24,830
当一切清晰起来时  已经太晚
And it all becomes clear way too late.

757
00:48:27,890 --> 00:48:30,230
其他任何人都不会真正明白
And no one else truly understands.

758
00:48:31,490 --> 00:48:33,650
除了就任过的人
Except someone who's been in the office...

759
00:48:36,160 --> 00:48:37,440
你不能指望这个职位
You can't expect the office

760
00:48:37,450 --> 00:48:39,990
能放大你的能力
to do anything more than what you bring to it.

761
00:48:42,550 --> 00:48:45,160
-我这么做是为党的利益  -我知道
- I'm doing this for the party. - I know.

762
00:48:46,050 --> 00:48:47,390
这令人钦佩
And it's admirable.

763
00:48:55,150 --> 00:48:56,240
特莉莎怎么样
How's Tricia?

764
00:48:57,450 --> 00:48:59,750
我们挺好  虽然花了些时间
Well, it's taken time, but we are good.

765
00:48:59,750 --> 00:49:01,430
孩子们也都很好
The kids are doing well.

766
00:49:02,750 --> 00:49:04,200
这只是开始
Well, this is just the beginning.

767
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:07,760
今后  你我会有更多的合作
You and I are gonna be working a lot more together from now on.

768
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:08,840
真的吗
Is that so?

769
00:49:26,430 --> 00:49:27,210
道格
Doug.

770
00:49:30,030 --> 00:49:32,230
汤姆  今天上午很忙
Tom, it's a busy morning.

771
00:49:32,230 --> 00:49:33,100
我现在不能提供任何引述
I don't have any quotes right now.

772
00:49:33,100 --> 00:49:35,280
等你有时间  我想坐下来
When you have a moment, i'd like to sit down

773
00:49:35,280 --> 00:49:37,580
问你几个关于丽萨·威廉姆斯的问题
and ask you some questions about Lisa Williams.

774
00:49:39,440 --> 00:49:41,010
不好意思  你在说什么
I'm sorry. What are you talking about?

775
00:49:42,100 --> 00:49:43,480
等你有时间  和我说一声  道格
Let me know when you're free, Doug.

776
00:49:44,060 --> 00:49:45,320
如果你想要一个声明
If you'd like a statement,

777
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:48,330
赛斯·格雷森的办公室很快会发一篇新闻稿
Seth Grayson's office will be issuing a press release shortly.

778
00:49:48,620 --> 00:49:51,160
你住在杜邦环岛附近  对吧
You live near Dupont Circle, don't you?

779
00:49:53,660 --> 00:49:55,810
我可以正式宣称  是的  我住那附近
I will go on the record and say yes, I do.

780
00:50:19,330 --> 00:50:20,480
沃克总统
President Walker,

781
00:50:21,220 --> 00:50:22,170
希瑟·邓巴的
it's been established in

782
00:50:22,170 --> 00:50:24,970
特别检察官报告中明确称
Heather Dunbar's special prosecutor's report

783
00:50:24,990 --> 00:50:25,650
我们有理由...
that we have reason to--

784
00:50:25,650 --> 00:50:28,870
议员  我已向主席
Congressman, as I mentioned to the chair

785
00:50:28,870 --> 00:50:31,140
和委员会的其他成员提过
and the other distinguished members of the committee,

786
00:50:31,180 --> 00:50:32,860
我建议我的委托人
I am advising my client

787
00:50:33,340 --> 00:50:36,660
目前对关于他就任美国总统期间的所有问题
to plead the Fifth at this time for all questions regarding his tenure

788
00:50:36,660 --> 00:50:39,100
行使第五修正案的权利
as President of the United States of America.

789
00:50:42,010 --> 00:50:45,200
同为民主党人  我得说
I must say, uh, that as a fellow Democrat,

790
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:47,260
这很不寻常
this is highly irregular.

791
00:50:47,570 --> 00:50:50,580
是的  议员  的确
Yes, Congressman, yes.

792
00:50:50,740 --> 00:50:52,070
但鉴于目前进行的调查...
But in light of ongoing investigations--

793
00:50:52,070 --> 00:50:55,350
其实  我愿意回答议员的问题
Actually, I will answer the congressman's questions.

794
00:51:00,150 --> 00:51:02,140
请提问吧
Please, ask your question.

795
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:06,420
你任总统期间
Under your administration,

796
00:51:06,420 --> 00:51:08,230
有来自中国商人的数百万美元资金
millions of dollars were illegally laundered

797
00:51:08,230 --> 00:51:11,100
经非法洗钱  影响了美国大选
from Chinese businessmen to affect American elections.

798
00:51:11,780 --> 00:51:12,770
是真的吗
Is this true?

799
00:51:14,120 --> 00:51:15,330
对  是真的
Yes. That's true.

800
00:51:17,170 --> 00:51:18,750
你能否告诉我们
And can you tell us what, if any,

801
00:51:18,750 --> 00:51:20,500
时任副总统弗兰西斯·安德伍德
was then Vice President Francis Underwood's

802
00:51:20,500 --> 00:51:22,530
在其中的参与情况  如果有的话
involvement in this scheme?

803
00:51:23,850 --> 00:51:27,280
他似乎是其中一名总设计师
Well, it appeared to me, he was one of its chief architects.

804
00:51:31,050 --> 00:51:33,660
你这话是什么意思  先生
And, uh, what exactly do you mean by that, sir?

805
00:51:35,090 --> 00:51:36,410
那是他的主意
It was his idea.

806
00:51:39,340 --> 00:51:41,610
马克  你还是去别的地方吧
Mark, I think you need to be elsewhere right now.

807
00:51:41,610 --> 00:51:43,520
我们要对此采取回避态度吗
Are we gonna bury our heads in the sand with this?

808
00:51:45,420 --> 00:51:47,120
不是  你要离开
No, you're going to leave,

809
00:51:47,120 --> 00:51:50,130
副总统和我来决定怎么做
and the vice president and I are going to decide what to do.

810
00:51:50,140 --> 00:51:51,740
沃克食言了  我们说好了的
Walker reneged. We had a deal.

811
00:51:51,740 --> 00:51:53,570
如果需要你  我们会告诉你的
We will let you know if you are needed.

812
00:51:53,570 --> 00:51:55,670
-先生  -这不是请求
- Sir... - That was not a request.

813
00:52:00,660 --> 00:52:02,860
你为什么非要去和他谈
Why did you have to go talk to him?

814
00:52:05,510 --> 00:52:07,480
一定会有出路的  弗兰西斯
There has to be a way out, Francis.

815
00:52:10,140 --> 00:52:12,630
是吗  有吗
Does there? Is there?

816
00:52:13,900 --> 00:52:15,720
这就是我的总统任期吗
Or is this my presidency?

817
00:52:16,640 --> 00:52:19,080
永远是攻击目标
Forever with a target on my back.

818
00:52:19,790 --> 00:52:21,680
被纠缠  被追捕
Haunted and hunted.

819
00:52:34,690 --> 00:52:37,740
莉安  如果你听到这个  说明我死了
LeAnn, if you're hearing this, it means that I'm dead.

820
00:53:19,830 --> 00:53:28,330
